# Rule: Audit and Fix OpenMCF Catalog System

**Purpose**: Guide an AI agent through auditing and fixing the docs catalog system infrastructure. This covers the build pipeline, provider display configuration, sidebar rendering, icon resolution, slug generation, link rewriting, and preset handling -- everything between source `catalog-page.md` files and the rendered docs site.

**Trigger**: User references this rule, reports a display issue in the docs catalog sidebar or catalog pages, asks to add a new provider to the catalog, or asks to fix catalog rendering problems.

**Scope boundary**: This rule covers the catalog **system infrastructure** (build scripts, React components, configuration maps). For auditing individual **catalog page content** (the markdown files), use the `audit-openmcf-component-catalog-page` rule in `_rules/docs/`.

---

## Source of Truth

The canonical authority for provider definitions is `cloud_resource_provider.proto`:

```
apis/org/openmcf/shared/cloudresourcekind/cloud_resource_provider.proto
```

Every provider enum value has a `provider_meta` annotation with `group` and `display_name`. The catalog system must reflect these values. When auditing, always read this proto first.

---

## System File Inventory

Read these files during any catalog system audit:

### Build Scripts (run at build time, produce static output)

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `site/scripts/copy-component-docs.ts` | Main build script. Scans `apis/org/openmcf/provider/` for catalog pages, extracts titles, strips provider prefixes, generates slugs, rewrites internal links, copies presets, generates provider index pages. Contains `PROVIDER_DISPLAY_NAMES` and `PROVIDER_PREFIXES` maps. |
| `site/scripts/generate-docs-structure.ts` | Scans `site/public/docs/` after copy-docs runs. Reads frontmatter from all markdown files and produces `site/public/docs-structure.json`, which drives the sidebar and catalog grid at runtime. |

### React Components (render at runtime from docs-structure.json)

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `site/src/app/docs/components/DocsSidebar.tsx` | Sidebar component. Loads `docs-structure.json`, renders provider directories with `ProviderIcon`, renders component items with per-component icons (letter-badge fallback). Uses `item.title` from the structure for display labels. |
| `site/src/app/docs/components/CatalogProviderGrid.tsx` | Catalog index grid. Renders provider cards with icon, display title, and component count. Uses `provider.title` from the `CatalogProvider` interface. |
| `site/src/app/docs/components/ProviderIcon.tsx` | Provider icon component. Resolves SVG path via `getProviderIconPath()`, falls back to a letter badge on load error. |
| `site/src/app/docs/utils/providerIcons.ts` | Icon path resolution. Convention: `/images/providers/{provider}.svg`. Override map (`PROVIDER_ICON_OVERRIDES`) for non-standard filenames. |
| `site/src/app/docs/[[...slug]]/page.tsx` | Page component. Contains `extractCatalogProviders()` which reads provider metadata from docs-structure.json and passes it to `CatalogProviderGrid`. |

### Static Assets

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `site/public/images/providers/*.svg` | Provider icon SVGs. Not all providers have icons; `ProviderIcon` falls back to a letter badge. |
| `site/public/images/providers/{provider}/{component}/logo.svg` | Per-component icons. Used by sidebar for component-level items. |

---

## Configuration Maps That Must Stay in Sync

When a provider is added, renamed, or removed, all four maps below must be updated. A mismatch causes display bugs.

### 1. `PROVIDER_DISPLAY_NAMES` in `copy-component-docs.ts`

Maps provider directory name to uppercase display name used in provider index pages, sidebar, and catalog grid.

```
directory name -> "DISPLAY NAME"
```

Source of truth: `display_name` in `cloud_resource_provider.proto`, uppercased.

### 2. `PROVIDER_PREFIXES` in `copy-component-docs.ts`

Maps provider directory name to prefix strings that `stripProviderPrefix()` removes from catalog page H1 headings to produce sidebar labels.

```
directory name -> ["Prefix1 ", "Prefix2 "]
```

Each prefix must end with a trailing space. The function tries each prefix in order and strips the first match.

### 3. `PROVIDER_ICON_OVERRIDES` in `providerIcons.ts`

Maps provider directory name to icon SVG path when the filename does not follow the `{provider}.svg` convention.

Only providers with non-standard icon filenames need entries. Providers without an SVG at all do not need an entry -- `ProviderIcon` falls back to a letter badge automatically.

### 4. `CatalogProvider` interface in `CatalogProviderGrid.tsx`

The interface shape must include `name`, `title`, `path`, and `componentCount`. The `extractCatalogProviders()` function in `page.tsx` populates these from docs-structure.json.

